I'm not saying the problem doesn't exist pre-high level pre-uber equipment, but from my point of view, agro didn't happen till later levels with good equipment, thus my suggestion.<br>
At level 55 lower the delay on evade to be that of backstab.  (i.e. make haste affect it).  Along with this, lower the chance to suceed on evade.  I believe it's ~66% atm...lower it to ~55%. As you level towards 60, have that success rate increase.  (Something along the lines of at 56=~57%, 57=~60%, 58=~63%, 59=~66%, 60=~69%)<br>
<br>
Your probably asking, &quot;Why lower the success rate?&quot;<br>
Well, I'm trying to think in terms of game balance.  I don't think Verant wants rogues to be able to not be on the hate list at all, thus they changed Evade along time ago to where you drop between 2nd-3rd, and not to the bottom.  And hasting the hide button may do just that, at that level, throw evade battle balance out of whack.  So my suggestion of lowering the success, but increasing the frequency may help keep that in line giving the equipment available at that level.  As they level towards 60, better equipment comes to them, increasing agro. Implementing the above system, with increased agro, comes increased success to evade.<br>
<br>
Good idea, bad idea? /shrug  I know I would hate to see it lowered to 55%, since I seem to fail whenever I really need it to work.  But I think a 66% chance to evade every 4-6 seconds all the time may be overpowering until you have the type of equipment needed for it. (Say..Max haste, 0.7 ratio weapons and higher..) <p><center><font size=1><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=7500>E v e r t o r r n__D a r k H e a r t</a><br>59 Blackguard <BR>
